BFN 

  [Text] Since the beginning of the year, 48,403 crimes have 
been uncovered in the Russian economic sphere, which is 16 
percent more than in the same period last year, the chief 
directorate on economic crime of the Russian Federation Interior 
Ministry has reported. 
  Experts point out the rising trend in violations of rules on 
currency operations. These have increased by almost 150 
percent, and number 3,800 cases. Most crimes of this kind 
concern illegal operations with hard currency and precious 
metals and stones. 
  As usual, the biggest increase among economic crimes is in 
crimes linked with the manufacture and sale of counterfeit money 
and securities. 

